## 1b. DOCUMENTATION CONSISTENCY — mandatory when changing any ADR

**Rule: When you modify an ADR, you MUST check and update all ADRs it cross-references.**

The doc set is designed for "no developer questions" mode. A contradiction between ADRs means a
developer will guess — which means bugs. Before finishing any ADR change:

1. Read the "impacted by" list below for the ADR you changed.
2. Open each impacted ADR and verify the change doesn't contradict it.
3. If it does, update the impacted ADR with a dated note or corrected content.
4. Update this `.cursorrules` file if canonical values change.

### ADR cross-reference map (which ADRs impact which)

| ADR | Impacted by / cross-references |
|-----|-------------------------------|
| **ADR-009** (UI layout) | ADR-028 (component adoption), ADR-032 (confirmation dialogs), ADR-035 (deep linking). Commands panel and outstanding side panel are **deferred to post-v1**. |
| **ADR-010** (Picture import) | ADR-026 (backend storage), ADR-033 (frontend upload grid). Browser uses file picker + drag-and-drop, NOT directory picker. |
| **ADR-003** (Customer model) | ADR-017 (schema mapping: purchase → orders + order_items, customer_address → addresses). |
| **ADR-004** (Shipper) | ADR-017, ADR-031 (schema mapping: purchase/shipment → orders table with tracking_number). |
| **ADR-006** (Reports scope) | ADR-017, ADR-013, ADR-036; includes profit-by-item, tax summary, inventory aging, accounting export (038/039/054/056). |
